<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-05T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1641.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-05T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Present this Government’s congratulations to the new President of whose
                            inauguration we have just learned. We wish for Jiménez and his country
                            undisturbed peace, great prosperity and continued progress. We hope that
                            all factions will unite in patriotic support of the Government and enter
                            into friendly rivalry for the promotion of the common good. The
                            Commander of the vessels there will receive from the Navy Department
                            instructions for the maintenance of order and the proper administration
                            of the Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>